MOOSE MITCHELL bumped leaving the gate, got impeded by HOIST THE GOLD crossing in front early, altered in from behind rival on the turn, moved out in the lane and could not rally. BRICKYARD RIDE dueled from inside early then cleared at the half-mile pole, challenged at the three-eighths pole, lost command at the five-sixteenths marker and retreated. VIVIR CON ALEGRIA (CHI) dueled outside BRICKYARD ride early then chased past the half-mile pole, got crowded at the five-sixteenths pole and faded in the lane. GO JOE WON got bumped on both sides at the start, chased off the rail, ran with his head high at the half-mile pole and steered out, came four to five wide into the lane, eased and walked off.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: DEL MAR RACE 11 1M Turf CR: 90. Maiden Claiming Purse 46000. FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 121 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Claiming Price $62,500, For Each $2,500 To $50,000 1 lb. (Rail at 12 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: RAHM stalked a bit off the rail early, remained near the inside then chased two wide into the stretch, moved out and launched a bid four deep into the final furlong, dueled with ST IGNACIO in deep stretch and gamely prevailed. ST IGNACIO pulled along the inside early, continued to tug the rider at times up the backstretch, drew closer still along the fence through the far turn, tipped out but ran into traffic briefly before splitting foes in upper stretch, dueled with RAHM in the late stages and got outkicked. RUSSELLS HUSTLE unhurried early on and moved inside, gained around the far turn while moving from the rail to the two path, angled out at the top of the lane, put in a mild late bid and got up for third. CRYPTO MAN traveled in mid-pack between rivals or in the two path, moved out and came four wide into the lane, bid six deep at the eighth pole but faltered in the deep stretch. HARD TIMES vied for command from outside early then chased two wide around the clubhouse turn, coaxed along thee deep into the lane, bid five deep with a furlong remaining but also faltered in the late stages. ADMIRAL HALSEY broke alertly then rated keen in the two path on the inside, continued up close through the middle stages, bid outside at the quarter pole, took over in upper stretch but yielded in the final sixteenth. STORMIN MIDNIGHT traveled three deep in mid-pack, bothered by CRYPTO MAN past the three-eighths pole, navigated that turn three to four wide and failed to menace. CHURCHMEISTER broke a step slow, trailed on the inside into the first turn, was on the move while steering out on the far turn, came five wide into the lane and flattened out. GAELIC NATION (IRE) broke a step slow, moved to the inside racing towards the rear, saved ground to the stretch, then came off the rail and failed to make an impact. NOBEL GARY chased briefly then split the rivals to take the lead, cleared and moved over to the inside, showed the way to the far turn, challenged from outside at the quarter pole, clung to a narrow lead into the stretch, relinquished the lead in upper stretch and weakened.
